WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:08.617
- Previously on "Happy!"...

00:08.660 --> 00:10.227
- I run the third largest
network in the nation.

00:10.271 --> 00:11.663
I have everything
a man could wish for.

00:11.707 --> 00:13.491
- What about the things
a man shouldn't wish for?

00:13.535 --> 00:15.798
[people screaming]

00:15.841 --> 00:17.278
- Run back to Sonny Shine?

00:17.321 --> 00:20.020
Go get high with the man who
kidnapped your own daughter?

00:20.063 --> 00:22.109
- Sonny Shine kidnapped me?
- Yeah.

00:22.152 --> 00:23.936
- Why didn't you tell me?

00:23.980 --> 00:25.460
- I thought I was doing
what was best for you.

00:25.503 --> 00:27.636
- I hate you both.

00:27.679 --> 00:30.291
- Hailey!

00:30.334 --> 00:32.380
- Now, to show you
that I come in peace,

00:32.423 --> 00:36.384
I'm going to retrieve
Ms. Hanson for you.

00:36.427 --> 00:38.603
- Later, sucker.

00:40.170 --> 00:41.737
- There, there, little lamb.

00:41.780 --> 00:43.695
Come inside.

00:43.739 --> 00:44.957
- Oh, hell, no!

00:45.001 --> 00:47.134
Nick? Nick.

00:47.177 --> 00:48.700
- [groans]
Where's Hailey?

00:48.744 --> 00:51.834
- It's bad, Nick.
She's with the bunny-eye guy!

00:53.879 --> 00:55.490
- [sighs]

00:56.578 --> 00:59.102
[siren wailing,
tires screech]

00:59.146 --> 01:02.323
[suspenseful music]

01:02.366 --> 01:04.934
♪

01:04.977 --> 01:07.937
[radio chatter]

01:07.980 --> 01:11.332
♪

01:11.375 --> 01:13.899
- Oh, crap, did I butt-dial
911 again?

01:13.943 --> 01:15.336
- Get down!
Get the fuck down!

01:15.379 --> 01:17.338
- Okay, everyone relax.
Take it easy.

01:17.381 --> 01:19.253
- I will empty this gun
into your fucking face.

01:19.296 --> 01:21.255
- Okay, but I'm gonna need
your car first.

01:21.298 --> 01:23.518
- I will shoot you
in the head, neck, and chest

01:23.561 --> 01:25.781
until I am
completely out of ammo!

01:25.824 --> 01:29.480
[seethes]
- Mm, sounds reasonable.

01:29.524 --> 01:32.353
You're gonna need
ibuprofen, boys.

01:32.396 --> 01:33.789
♪

01:33.832 --> 01:35.921
- Car 1103, please respond.

01:35.965 --> 01:39.403
We've got a code 8 in need
of additional officers.

01:39.447 --> 01:40.491
Home disturbance, shots fired.

01:40.535 --> 01:42.145
- Car 1103,
and I got to tell you

01:42.189 --> 01:43.973
that all these reports about
a disturbance at this residence

01:44.016 --> 01:45.627
are greatly exaggerated.

01:45.670 --> 01:49.457
Now, the tenants have agreed
to turn down the fucking noise,

01:49.500 --> 01:51.285
clean up after their pets,

01:51.328 --> 01:53.809
and wear some fucking underwear
when the curtains are open.

01:53.852 --> 01:56.290
[bell dings]

01:56.333 --> 01:58.030
- Officer, please state
your badge number.

01:58.074 --> 01:59.554
[car horn blares]

01:59.597 --> 02:02.992
- Uh, yeah, I'm gonna have
to get back to you on, uh--

02:03.035 --> 02:04.994
on that one there, dispatch.

02:05.037 --> 02:06.996
[grunts]
[object clatters]

02:07.039 --> 02:08.519
All right, Hap.

02:08.563 --> 02:09.999
Let's go get her.

02:10.042 --> 02:12.828
- You're gonna want to hang
a right up here toward 278.

02:12.871 --> 02:15.004
[tires squealing]

02:15.047 --> 02:18.007
[suspenseful music]

02:18.050 --> 02:19.487
♪

02:19.530 --> 02:21.489
- This it?

02:21.532 --> 02:28.583
♪

02:32.543 --> 02:34.502
Hmm?

02:34.545 --> 02:36.852
[panel chirps, whirs]
Ah...

02:36.895 --> 02:39.507
[chuckles]

02:39.550 --> 02:43.032
[grunting]

02:43.075 --> 02:45.991
[sniffs]

02:46.035 --> 02:49.299
♪

03:13.889 --> 03:17.284
- Oh, Nick, we did it!

03:25.770 --> 03:29.818
[eerie music]

03:29.861 --> 03:32.168
[lights clang]

03:32.212 --> 03:37.782
♪

03:37.826 --> 03:39.741
[lights clang]

03:39.784 --> 03:41.743
[beeping]

03:41.786 --> 03:44.876
♪

03:44.920 --> 03:47.270
Oh, nothing gives my tongue
a tickle like the taste

03:47.314 --> 03:49.707
of a pickled...

03:49.751 --> 03:53.276
♪

03:53.320 --> 03:56.497
[rats squeaking]

03:56.540 --> 04:03.591
♪

04:37.668 --> 04:40.802
- [sniffs]
Nick, I-I think that's--

04:40.845 --> 04:43.326
- Pee-pee, Hap.

04:43.370 --> 04:45.807
It's pee-pee.

04:45.850 --> 04:48.810
[foreboding music]

04:48.853 --> 04:55.904
♪

05:08.873 --> 05:10.222
Pretty cool rabbit's foot.

05:10.266 --> 05:11.920
I wonder what happened
to the rest of him?

05:11.963 --> 05:14.705
- It's for luck.

05:14.749 --> 05:17.882
♪

05:17.926 --> 05:21.408
- Oh, Hap...

05:21.451 --> 05:23.671
it was right in front of me.

05:23.714 --> 05:25.716
♪

05:25.760 --> 05:29.372
He's been working her
this whole time.

05:29.416 --> 05:30.982
How the hell did I miss it?

05:31.026 --> 05:32.462
- It's not your fault, Nick.

05:32.506 --> 05:34.246
If anyone should have known
what she was going through,

05:34.290 --> 05:35.987
it was me.
[cell phone vibrating]

05:36.031 --> 05:38.860
But all I could think about
was my own dumb hang-ups.

05:38.903 --> 05:40.601
- Hap.

05:40.644 --> 05:42.167
Hailey!

05:42.211 --> 05:44.344
- And the harder the big,
hairy, stupid monkey tried

05:44.387 --> 05:48.913
to free himself from the trap,
the tighter the trap closed.

05:48.957 --> 05:50.350
- Where is she?

05:50.393 --> 05:52.526
- So you've happened
onto my groovy little pad.

05:52.569 --> 05:55.224
What a shame.
I really like this place.

05:55.267 --> 05:56.704
So many fond memories.

05:56.747 --> 05:58.401
- Yeah, we took the tour.
It's cozy.

05:58.445 --> 05:59.750
So why don't you come home
to daddy?

05:59.794 --> 06:01.273
We'll Netflix and chill
together.

06:01.317 --> 06:03.188
- I'm going to press
a button now.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.886
Good-bye, monkey.
- Smoothie--

06:04.929 --> 06:08.150
[phone line beeping]
[distant explosion]

06:08.193 --> 06:10.979
- Uh, Nick?
- Was that my stomach?

06:11.022 --> 06:14.809
[distant explosion]

06:14.852 --> 06:16.376
[Happy squeaks]

06:16.419 --> 06:19.422
[steady bluegrass music]

06:19.466 --> 06:21.424
- ♪ Mr. Rabbit, Mr. Rabbit

06:21.468 --> 06:23.426
♪ Your ears are mighty long

06:23.470 --> 06:26.908
♪ Yes, bless God,
they was put on wrong ♪

06:26.951 --> 06:30.738
♪ Every little soul
must shine, shine ♪

06:30.781 --> 06:34.481
♪ Every little soul
gonna shine ♪

06:37.614 --> 06:39.486
[both coughing]

06:42.314 --> 06:44.099
[cell phone vibrating]

06:44.142 --> 06:46.406
- [coughing]

06:46.449 --> 06:48.408
I'm gonna hollow out your head
like a pumpkin,

06:48.451 --> 06:49.757
you motherfucker.

06:49.800 --> 06:52.281
- Dad.

06:52.324 --> 06:54.544
- Hailey, Hailey, sweetheart--

06:54.588 --> 06:56.720
- You have to stop
trying to find me.

06:56.764 --> 06:58.853
I'm safe.
[sirens approaching]

06:58.896 --> 07:00.463
- No, no.

07:00.507 --> 07:02.900
No, listen to me.
Listen to me.

07:02.944 --> 07:05.773
He's lying to you, baby.
- No, Dad.

07:05.816 --> 07:07.949
You're the only one
who lied to me.

07:07.992 --> 07:09.167
You and Mom.

07:09.211 --> 07:11.387
I understand why
you thought you had to,

07:11.431 --> 07:13.389
but I'm done being lied to.

07:13.433 --> 07:15.391
- Hailey.
[phone line beeps]

07:15.435 --> 07:18.394
[siren wailing]

07:18.438 --> 07:20.091
[car doors open]

07:20.135 --> 07:21.266
- Nick!

07:29.013 --> 07:31.189
- Excuse me, miss--

07:33.975 --> 07:35.019
- Who is this woman?

07:35.063 --> 07:37.021
- Ms. McCarthy,
the police officer--

07:37.065 --> 07:38.762
- Yep.

07:42.418 --> 07:43.375
[door closes]

07:43.419 --> 07:45.465
- Kap Gostynski.
- Yes, I am.

07:45.508 --> 07:48.250
- Last of the big-time moguls.

07:48.293 --> 07:49.817
Kind of a legend, aren't you?

07:49.860 --> 07:51.471
- Tell the Emmys.
- [laughs]

07:51.514 --> 07:53.603
Thank you for seeing me.
- Why wouldn't I?

07:53.647 --> 07:56.519
I'm always happy to cooperate
with New York's finest.

07:56.563 --> 07:59.174
And I do mean...

07:59.217 --> 08:01.263
"finest."

08:01.306 --> 08:04.614
- Sonny Shine.

08:04.658 --> 08:06.398
- A one-in-a-million talent.

08:06.442 --> 08:08.183
Smile that lights up
the screen.

08:08.226 --> 08:11.316
- I'm more interested in his
talents behind the camera.

08:11.360 --> 08:13.188
[tense music]

08:13.231 --> 08:16.670
- "Behind the camera"?

08:16.713 --> 08:20.151
- I've seen the tape, Kap.

08:20.195 --> 08:23.285
You're a hungry boy.

08:23.328 --> 08:24.547
- Amazing how realistic

08:24.591 --> 08:26.897
Hollywood special effects are
these days.

08:26.941 --> 08:28.333
♪

08:28.377 --> 08:30.814
- You're a busy man,
so I'll get right to the point.

08:30.858 --> 08:34.165
Sonny's Easter Eggtacular--
the show cannot air.

08:34.209 --> 08:36.428
You couldn't possibly
understand the reasons why.

08:36.472 --> 08:38.213
I barely
understand them myself.

08:38.256 --> 08:39.954
But if that show is broadcast,

08:39.997 --> 08:41.651
the results will be
catastrophic.

08:41.695 --> 08:43.044
- "Catastrophic"?

08:43.087 --> 08:44.698
You're telling me.

08:44.741 --> 08:48.049
That Easter special
is an abomination.

08:48.092 --> 08:50.268
At this point, I'm convinced
a video of me eating

08:50.312 --> 08:53.663
my nephew's tartar would be
less damaging to my career

08:53.707 --> 08:55.926
than airing that piece of shit.

08:55.970 --> 08:57.754
- You're the only at
the network keeping it alive.

08:57.798 --> 09:00.540
You can cancel his sequined ass
with one phone call.

09:00.583 --> 09:03.412
- As you said...

09:03.455 --> 09:04.979
I'm a busy man.

09:05.022 --> 09:08.504
- Sonny doesn't believe
in digital, Kap.

09:08.548 --> 09:11.551
"Tape is forever," he says.

09:11.594 --> 09:13.901
There's only one copy,
and I have it.

09:13.944 --> 09:15.380
Cancel the show.

09:15.424 --> 09:17.426
I'll give you the tape and let
you destroy it yourself.

09:17.469 --> 09:21.430
♪

09:21.473 --> 09:23.606
- This is turning into
a bad scene.

09:23.650 --> 09:26.696
First of all, I'm not buying
you as a lady cop.

09:26.740 --> 09:29.569
You got the sexy part,
although a low-cut blouse,

09:29.612 --> 09:31.440
preferably in a bold,
primary color,

09:31.483 --> 09:32.963
would helpful
in that department,

09:33.007 --> 09:34.617
but where's
the no-nonsense blazer

09:34.661 --> 09:36.880
that says, "I can hold my own
in a man's world,

09:36.924 --> 09:38.708
pinch my bottom
at your own peril"?

09:38.752 --> 09:41.058
- I have that blazer.
- Sure you do.

09:41.102 --> 09:42.277
And the hairstyle--

09:42.320 --> 09:44.366
I understand the appeal
of no muss, no fuss,

09:44.409 --> 09:47.848
but you look like you're here
to sell me an investment condo.

09:47.891 --> 09:51.025
Sorry, doll, I know bad acting
when I see it.

09:51.068 --> 09:53.941
You're bluffing.

09:53.984 --> 09:57.771
- I thought
you might say that.

09:57.814 --> 10:00.774
Sorry I wasted your time,
Gostynski.

10:00.817 --> 10:03.037
- I'll enjoy
watching you leave.

10:03.080 --> 10:10.000
♪

10:14.178 --> 10:17.225
[truck horn blaring]

10:21.621 --> 10:24.536
- How much farther?

10:24.580 --> 10:27.017
- We're close now.

10:29.411 --> 10:31.326
- Who were those men...

10:31.369 --> 10:32.675
at the house?

10:32.719 --> 10:35.330
- Your father's made
a lot of enemies.

10:35.373 --> 10:37.811
That's something
that he might have considered

10:37.854 --> 10:40.335
when he came back
into your life.

10:41.771 --> 10:44.731
But that's parents.
[chuckles]

10:44.774 --> 10:48.169
They don't see their children
as individuals.

10:48.212 --> 10:51.259
They only see them
as a reflection of themselves.

10:53.783 --> 10:56.699
- Where are we?

10:56.743 --> 11:01.225
- Someplace that I haven't been
in a very long time.

11:01.269 --> 11:02.705
- What about Sonny?

11:02.749 --> 11:04.620
You said he--
- Don't worry.

11:04.664 --> 11:06.840
We'll be safe here, and...

11:06.883 --> 11:09.756
then we'll decide what we'll do
about you-know-who.

11:14.674 --> 11:16.850
[car horn honks]

11:18.155 --> 11:22.029
- $22.82.

11:22.072 --> 11:24.814
Diesel, pump four, and these.

11:24.858 --> 11:26.294
I need to go number one.

11:26.337 --> 11:28.165
[door opens, bells jingle]
You wait here for me.

11:28.209 --> 11:30.994
Oh...
and order the cherry soda.

11:31.038 --> 11:34.084
It's delicious here.

11:34.128 --> 11:35.216
- It was on the news.

11:35.259 --> 11:36.696
Can't believe you didn't
hear about that.

11:36.739 --> 11:38.001
- No.

11:38.045 --> 11:39.742
- Kid only must have been 12,
13 years old.

11:39.786 --> 11:40.961
- Unbelievable.

11:41.004 --> 11:42.397
A-and no one ever knew
why he did it?

11:42.440 --> 11:45.008
- Said he just wanted
to prove it was possible.

11:45.052 --> 11:47.576
[laughs]
Little dude just stood there

11:47.619 --> 11:49.404
at the junior high
science fair.

11:49.447 --> 11:52.146
All the other kids
and their parents walking by.

11:52.189 --> 11:54.365
Standing next to the jar.

11:54.409 --> 11:56.846
- His own nuts
floating in the jar.

11:56.890 --> 11:58.500
His nuts.

11:58.543 --> 12:00.720
Get the fuck out of here.
- I shit you not.

12:00.763 --> 12:03.026
Just looking everyone
in the eye.

12:03.070 --> 12:05.289
No shame, no pride.

12:05.333 --> 12:07.335
Just zippo.

12:07.378 --> 12:09.337
Said he cut them off himself.

12:09.380 --> 12:12.035
Surgical, with a straight ra--

12:12.079 --> 12:15.038
[tense music]

12:15.082 --> 12:17.475
♪

12:17.519 --> 12:20.783
Had to be 30 years ago.

12:20.827 --> 12:23.220
Wonder whatever happened
to the little bastard?

12:23.264 --> 12:25.005
- Probably ended up
in Congress.

12:25.048 --> 12:27.137
[both laughing]

12:27.181 --> 12:29.749
- Or in Hollywood.
[both laughing]

12:29.792 --> 12:33.796
♪

12:33.840 --> 12:35.232
- [sighs]

12:35.276 --> 12:36.581
[urine splashing]

12:36.625 --> 12:38.845
[door opens,
splashing stops]

12:38.888 --> 12:40.760
[footsteps approaching]

12:40.803 --> 12:43.414
[door squeaks, closes,
lock clicks]

12:43.458 --> 12:44.894
[toilet seat clatters]

12:44.938 --> 12:47.723
[man spits]

12:47.767 --> 12:51.422
♪

12:51.466 --> 12:53.337
[splashing continues]

12:53.381 --> 12:57.254
- Been a spell since y'all
and myself done caught up.

12:57.298 --> 13:04.087
♪

13:04.131 --> 13:07.395
- Oh.
[sighs]

13:09.136 --> 13:12.356
I've had my hands full.

13:12.400 --> 13:14.619
Incidentally,
this is Upstate New York,

13:14.663 --> 13:16.404
not Pickens County, Alabama.

13:16.447 --> 13:21.104
- You are wearing a lot of hats
these days, Smoother--

13:21.148 --> 13:23.280
bunny hat,

13:23.324 --> 13:26.327
working for Sonny Shine hat,

13:26.370 --> 13:30.810
conspiring to kill
the very same Sonny Shine hat,

13:30.853 --> 13:35.249
gaslighting and programming
his pint-sized assassin hat.

13:35.292 --> 13:38.556
- It's nothing
that I can't handle.

13:38.600 --> 13:40.732
The plan is proceeding along
perfectly.

13:40.776 --> 13:42.038
- So you say.

13:42.082 --> 13:46.303
But I have my nagging doubts.

13:46.347 --> 13:49.350
This girl, it don't seem
much like she'd be ready

13:49.393 --> 13:52.614
to do what needs to be done,
now, do it?

13:54.007 --> 13:57.140
- She'll be ready.

13:57.184 --> 14:01.841
I have broken down everything
that she ever believed in.

14:01.884 --> 14:03.799
There's nothing left.

14:03.843 --> 14:06.889
Just a blank page
waiting to be written.

14:06.933 --> 14:08.369
- Mm-hmm.

14:08.412 --> 14:13.156
But I know when someone
has made a friend of death.

14:13.200 --> 14:15.071
♪

14:15.115 --> 14:17.465
And she...

14:17.508 --> 14:19.162
ain't done it.

14:19.206 --> 14:21.730
- You trusted me for a reason,

14:21.773 --> 14:24.559
and I will not disappoint you.

14:24.602 --> 14:26.996
All I need
is a little more ti--

14:27.040 --> 14:30.870
[toilet flushing, door opens]

14:30.913 --> 14:37.877
♪

14:39.356 --> 14:41.881
[door bells jingle]

14:41.924 --> 14:48.931
♪

14:50.715 --> 14:53.893
[harmonica playing tunelessly]

14:53.936 --> 14:57.026
♪

14:57.070 --> 14:59.899
- Would you stop that, please?

14:59.942 --> 15:01.378
- Sorry.

15:01.422 --> 15:04.164
- [sighs]

15:04.207 --> 15:07.515
What the fuck
was I thinking, Hap...

15:07.558 --> 15:09.865
trying to be
some kind of normal dad,

15:09.909 --> 15:13.434
trying to stick
to the straight and narrow?

15:15.523 --> 15:17.220
How was me being back
in their lives

15:17.264 --> 15:18.743
gonna end up any different?

15:18.787 --> 15:20.484
- You tried to do good, Nick.

15:20.528 --> 15:23.748
That's what matters.

15:23.792 --> 15:25.925
- [scoffs]

15:25.968 --> 15:27.491
No.

15:27.535 --> 15:30.930
Hap, that don't matter.

15:33.367 --> 15:36.544
I'm a virus.

15:36.587 --> 15:38.720
Everything I touch,

15:38.763 --> 15:41.418
everything anywhere near me
is bound to be infected

15:41.462 --> 15:43.899
sooner or later.

15:45.248 --> 15:47.163
Amanda...

15:47.207 --> 15:50.645
Hailey.

15:50.688 --> 15:53.430
I've lost everyone
that ever meant anything to me.

15:53.474 --> 15:56.781
- You haven't lost me.

15:56.825 --> 15:58.783
- What the hell
you still doing here, anyway?

15:58.827 --> 16:02.265
Shouldn't you be out
rutting with a...

16:02.309 --> 16:04.093
lawn ornament?

16:04.137 --> 16:06.313
- Yeah, I guess I deserve that.

16:06.356 --> 16:07.488
You're not the only one
who's had their head

16:07.531 --> 16:09.272
up their you-know-what lately.

16:09.316 --> 16:11.187
While you were trying
so hard to change,

16:11.231 --> 16:13.624
I was doing everything I could
not to.

16:13.668 --> 16:16.018
I lost sight
of what's really important,

16:16.062 --> 16:20.631
what being an imaginary friend
is all about.

16:20.675 --> 16:22.590
We can't
give up hope, Nick.

16:22.633 --> 16:24.157
[loud crunch]

16:24.200 --> 16:26.724
- [grunts, hollers]

16:30.032 --> 16:32.078
- [sighs]

16:32.121 --> 16:34.036
- I think I'm out of hope.

16:34.080 --> 16:36.343
- Well, I got enough hope
for the both of us.

16:36.386 --> 16:37.997
- Goody.
- I'm gonna find help, Nick.

16:38.040 --> 16:39.911
- You do that.
- I'll be back, I promise.

16:39.955 --> 16:43.306
But first, I got to make
with the Jackrabbit Parole.

16:43.350 --> 16:45.091
- What the--

16:50.009 --> 16:51.271
[ball clangs]

16:51.314 --> 16:53.142
God, I want to turn you
into a chess piece.

16:53.186 --> 16:55.144
- Oh, Sax.

16:55.188 --> 16:57.625
[sinister music]

16:57.668 --> 16:59.627
- We're coming
for you, asshole.

16:59.670 --> 17:02.282
- Uh, Nick?
- Yeah, asshole.

17:02.325 --> 17:04.023
- Listen to me.

17:04.066 --> 17:06.416
Get out of here.

17:06.460 --> 17:08.462
Well, well, well,
boys in blue.

17:08.505 --> 17:10.203
What took you so long?

17:10.246 --> 17:11.552
- Nick Sax.

17:11.595 --> 17:13.684
- That's what's sewn
into my underwear.

17:13.728 --> 17:15.643
- You used to be one of us.
- Yeah.

17:15.686 --> 17:17.079
- Yeah, look at you now.

17:17.123 --> 17:19.168
- Not to brag, but you should
see the other guys.

17:19.212 --> 17:21.649
[lock clicks]

17:21.692 --> 17:23.303
- You put some
of your ex-brothers

17:23.346 --> 17:24.739
in the hospital
last night, Sax.

17:24.782 --> 17:26.132
- Let me stop you right there.

17:26.175 --> 17:27.829
I can't believe you guys
came all the way down here

17:27.872 --> 17:29.352
just to recite a pretty speech,

17:29.396 --> 17:31.006
so why don't we just
get down to it?

17:31.050 --> 17:38.013
♪

17:38.057 --> 17:41.190
- This is it?

17:41.234 --> 17:43.236
- It's not much, I know.

17:43.279 --> 17:45.064
We weren't well off.

17:45.107 --> 17:46.369
- I didn't mean--

17:46.413 --> 17:48.328
- No, it's okay.

17:48.371 --> 17:51.070
- It's nice.

17:51.113 --> 17:52.419
Where is she?

17:52.462 --> 17:54.943
- Just a minute.

17:54.986 --> 18:02.037
♪

18:04.170 --> 18:06.215
[glass shattering]

18:06.259 --> 18:09.349
[door opens]

18:09.392 --> 18:11.481
No, no, no,
it's okay, Mom.

18:11.525 --> 18:14.963
Mama, mama, mama.

18:15.006 --> 18:16.921
Hailey.

18:16.965 --> 18:19.141
Meet Cheryl.

18:19.185 --> 18:20.403
- Hi.

18:20.447 --> 18:21.970
- Mama, this is, uh, Hailey.

18:22.013 --> 18:24.538
She's gonna be staying with us
for a while.

18:24.581 --> 18:26.235
- Mal de ojo.

18:26.279 --> 18:28.585
- No, no, no.
Tranquila, mama--

18:28.629 --> 18:30.283
- Mal de ojo.
- Tranquila, por favor.

18:30.326 --> 18:32.154
Yeah.
- Mal de ojo.

18:32.198 --> 18:35.636
- Mama, mama.
- [muttering in Spanish]

18:37.159 --> 18:39.379
- Te amo, mama.

18:41.729 --> 18:44.166
My biological mother
died in childbirth.

18:44.210 --> 18:45.733
My father met Cheryl.

18:45.776 --> 18:48.779
She's the only mother
I've ever known.

18:49.867 --> 18:53.044
- She seems so scared.
- [muttering in Spanish]

18:53.088 --> 18:54.568
- I'm sorry.

18:54.611 --> 18:58.311
It's the first time, uh,
that she's seen me...

18:58.354 --> 19:01.270
since...

19:02.358 --> 19:06.362
To be honest, Hailey, um,
she's been through a lot.

19:06.406 --> 19:08.364
We all have.

19:12.238 --> 19:14.327
[bitter, tense music]

19:14.370 --> 19:16.633
Because of him.

19:16.677 --> 19:18.157
- "Him"?

19:18.200 --> 19:20.159
♪

19:20.202 --> 19:21.421
- My...

19:21.464 --> 19:25.773
♪

19:25.816 --> 19:28.123
Let me, uh, show you
to your room. Come on.

19:28.167 --> 19:33.868
♪

19:33.911 --> 19:38.351
I know it's musty,
but, uh, you'll be safe here.

19:39.743 --> 19:42.006
- You're leaving?

19:42.050 --> 19:43.660
- There's something
that I need to do.

19:43.704 --> 19:46.663
I'll just be an hour,
and then we'll go for lunch.

19:46.707 --> 19:48.317
You must be starving.

19:48.361 --> 19:50.189
- No.

19:50.232 --> 19:51.668
You told me we'd make sure

19:51.712 --> 19:54.671
Sonny Shine never hurt anyone
ever again.

19:54.715 --> 19:56.717
You said you'd make everything
right again...

19:56.760 --> 19:59.676
for me, for my parents.

19:59.720 --> 20:02.375
But you never told me how.

20:02.418 --> 20:04.203
- You need to trust me.

20:04.246 --> 20:07.771
- But it'll never be right,
not until he's in jail forever.

20:07.815 --> 20:11.035
How can we do that from here?
Why are we running away?

20:11.079 --> 20:12.907
- We are not running away.

20:20.610 --> 20:22.569
A policeman told me
a story once

20:22.612 --> 20:25.267
about a child that was...

20:25.311 --> 20:26.747
taken.

20:26.790 --> 20:28.227
They caught the man
who did it,

20:28.270 --> 20:32.361
and he was, quite simply,
a monster.

20:32.405 --> 20:33.667
You know the type.

20:33.710 --> 20:35.538
- [screaming]

20:35.582 --> 20:38.628
- The child's father came
to see the policeman one night,

20:38.672 --> 20:40.108
and he was filled with rage.

20:40.151 --> 20:43.067
He said, "I don't care
about the laws.

20:43.111 --> 20:46.245
"Just let me in that cell
with him alone for 20 minutes.

20:46.288 --> 20:49.552
That's all I ask."

20:49.596 --> 20:52.338
Do you know
what the policeman said?

20:52.381 --> 20:55.123
♪

20:55.166 --> 20:58.909
He said, "The man in that cell
is a killer.

20:58.953 --> 21:01.347
"He knows what violence
means...

21:01.390 --> 21:05.002
"what it feels like,
what he's capable of.

21:05.046 --> 21:07.396
"He has made friends
with death.

21:07.440 --> 21:09.180
"You haven't.

21:09.224 --> 21:12.706
"If I let you in there
alone with him...

21:12.749 --> 21:15.274
you'll never come out."

21:15.317 --> 21:16.840
♪

21:16.884 --> 21:18.451
- I don't understand.

21:18.494 --> 21:21.758
♪

21:21.802 --> 21:24.283
- You'll get your revenge,
Hailey.

21:24.326 --> 21:26.589
I promise.

21:26.633 --> 21:29.853
[radio chatter]

21:31.725 --> 21:34.380
[indistinct chatter]

21:34.423 --> 21:36.033
[distant sirens wailing]

21:36.077 --> 21:38.993
- If you're looking
for your fuck-boy Sax,

21:39.036 --> 21:40.516
you're a little late.

21:40.560 --> 21:42.126
He's behind stripes.

21:42.170 --> 21:44.738
It's about time, if you ask me.

21:44.781 --> 21:46.653
- Not exactly news.

21:46.696 --> 21:49.308
Half the department ran code
on that APB.

21:49.351 --> 21:52.485
And he's not my fuck-boy.

21:52.528 --> 21:55.139
Speaking of which,
where's yours?

21:55.183 --> 21:57.403
- None of your beeswax,
McCarthy.

21:57.446 --> 21:58.839
- Look, forget I asked.

21:58.882 --> 22:01.668
- You know, some people
just have a different idea

22:01.711 --> 22:03.844
of what being
a good partner means...

22:03.887 --> 22:05.759
if you know what I mean.
- I don't.

22:05.802 --> 22:07.456
- Some people think
that they can have

22:07.500 --> 22:09.719
as many partners as they want
as long as they have a badge

22:09.763 --> 22:11.286
and two X chromosomes--

22:11.330 --> 22:13.636
- Okay, that's more information
than I ever needed to know.

22:13.680 --> 22:15.334
- Oh, fine.

22:15.377 --> 22:16.900
If you really must know,

22:16.944 --> 22:19.816
Hubble and I ain't exactly
on speaking terms right now.

22:19.860 --> 22:22.341
[distant siren wailing]

22:22.384 --> 22:24.517
- That's rough.

22:24.560 --> 22:27.041
I mean, who's gonna finish
your sentences for you?

22:27.084 --> 22:29.783
- Oh, that's really funny.

22:29.826 --> 22:31.350
You're a regular
Tig Notaro, McCarthy.

22:31.393 --> 22:34.222
- Listen to me,
I need to get to Sax.

22:34.265 --> 22:37.486
- Not gonna happen.
I'm sorry.

22:37.530 --> 22:39.227
Nick Sax
was taken into custody

22:39.270 --> 22:41.185
because he refused
to cooperate--

22:41.229 --> 22:44.319
- You're a dirty girl, Ace.

22:45.886 --> 22:48.018
You know, I'm dirty, too.

22:48.062 --> 22:50.369
The whole department's dirty.

22:50.412 --> 22:53.415
Doesn't mean we can't
throw each other a bone.

22:55.548 --> 22:57.201
- What, uh...

22:57.245 --> 23:01.858
what--what kind of bone
are you talking about?

23:01.902 --> 23:04.034
- I don't know
how deep in you are with Shine,

23:04.078 --> 23:07.037
what you know,
what you don't want to know,

23:07.081 --> 23:09.388
but I'm willing
to look the other way.

23:09.431 --> 23:10.693
Just get me Sax.

23:10.737 --> 23:13.479
- Oh, that kind of bone.
Right.

23:13.522 --> 23:15.611
- All I'm saying
is what's good for the goose

23:15.655 --> 23:18.484
is good for the...

23:18.527 --> 23:22.923
You know, geese in general.

23:25.708 --> 23:26.927
- You know, McCarthy,

23:26.970 --> 23:28.407
getting you kicked off
the force was--

23:28.450 --> 23:30.365
- Nothing personal.

23:30.409 --> 23:32.585
I know.

23:32.628 --> 23:36.066
How about that bone?

23:36.110 --> 23:39.461
- I think I could, uh,
see what I could do.

23:39.505 --> 23:42.464
[eerie music]

23:42.508 --> 23:49.558
♪

23:52.996 --> 23:55.869
[dark, curious music]

23:55.912 --> 24:02.963
♪

24:40.522 --> 24:44.047
[distant clatter]

24:44.091 --> 24:49.966
♪

24:50.010 --> 24:52.969
[teakettle whistling]

24:53.013 --> 24:59.976
♪

25:00.020 --> 25:02.544
[whistling stops]

25:03.632 --> 25:05.329
[light music playing on TV]

25:05.373 --> 25:06.809
- Listen.

25:06.853 --> 25:09.769
- Just a minute, now.
Don't monkey around.

25:09.812 --> 25:12.423
- What if I told you
I was crazy about you?

25:12.467 --> 25:14.861
- Who said you were,
and so what?

25:14.904 --> 25:18.995
- No, look,
what I mean, Johnny...

25:19.039 --> 25:20.997
I really like you.

25:21.041 --> 25:23.609
- I really like you, too.
Should I trust you?

25:23.652 --> 25:25.524
- Maybe I'd be good for you.

25:25.567 --> 25:27.526
- Now, wait a minute,
I'm not--

25:27.569 --> 25:30.529
[sweeping romantic music
playing on TV]

25:30.572 --> 25:33.009
♪

25:33.053 --> 25:34.184
[cell phone vibrates]

25:34.228 --> 25:36.491
- Oh, my.
- You all right?

25:36.535 --> 25:38.014
- Oh, I'm sorry...

25:38.058 --> 25:41.409
[conversation continues
indistinctly]

25:41.452 --> 25:44.281
[phone clicks]

25:44.325 --> 25:47.197
[line trilling]

25:47.241 --> 25:49.852
- Simon.
- Hey, you.

25:49.896 --> 25:52.115
I was hoping you'd call.
Is everything all right?

25:52.159 --> 25:54.727
- What are you doing--
I mean right now?

25:54.770 --> 25:57.120
- Just catching up on--
- Great.

25:57.164 --> 25:58.339
Fuck that.

25:58.382 --> 26:00.559
I'm in this...

26:00.602 --> 26:02.038
Um...

26:02.082 --> 26:03.692
♪

26:03.736 --> 26:05.999
I'm actually not quite sure
what it is,

26:06.042 --> 26:08.305
but I need you
to get over here right now

26:08.349 --> 26:10.873
and get in me.

26:10.917 --> 26:12.571
Can you do that?

26:12.614 --> 26:14.964
- Just finding a pencil.

26:15.008 --> 26:17.445
- Are you there?

26:17.488 --> 26:20.927
I need it now, motherfucker!

26:20.970 --> 26:22.581
- Amanda.

26:22.624 --> 26:26.410
Boy, is someone gonna have
a tummy ache tomorrow.

26:26.454 --> 26:28.499
- "You scoundrel," I said.

26:28.543 --> 26:32.286
"Would you ask Kyoko Kishida
to do that?"

26:32.329 --> 26:34.375
And then he said,

26:34.418 --> 26:35.855
"I have no recollection

26:35.898 --> 26:38.727
of Kyoko Kishida
working in pasties."

26:38.771 --> 26:41.164
[laughs]
- Bebe!

26:41.208 --> 26:42.905
- Oh, look who it is.

26:42.949 --> 26:44.820
My little whatchamacallit.

26:44.864 --> 26:47.823
- Happy, remember?
- Well, of course I do.

26:47.867 --> 26:49.782
You're the pool boy's
little pal.

26:49.825 --> 26:51.653
- Bebe, I need your help.
- Yes?

26:51.697 --> 26:53.612
- There's a lady inside,
Amanda Hansen,

26:53.655 --> 26:54.787
and she's in a lot of trouble.

26:54.830 --> 26:56.789
This is no place
for a nice, sweet mommy,

26:56.832 --> 26:58.573
let alone one
with a bun in the oven.

26:58.617 --> 27:00.053
We've got to get her
out of here.

27:00.096 --> 27:01.228
- Preggers, you say?

27:01.271 --> 27:04.492
Oh, well, say no more,
little poopsie.

27:04.535 --> 27:08.322
Aunt Bebe can handle this.

27:17.331 --> 27:18.680
Well...

27:18.724 --> 27:22.553
we are making ourselves
right at home, aren't we?

27:22.597 --> 27:24.773
- Hi!
- [laughs]

27:24.817 --> 27:26.645
Oh, I'll be you are.

27:26.688 --> 27:29.125
- Bebe, tell her
Nick is in jail.

27:29.169 --> 27:31.301
Tell her she's
in terrible danger being here.

27:31.345 --> 27:34.043
Tell her Sonny Shine is--

27:34.087 --> 27:36.219
- I'm sure that I need
no introduction,

27:36.263 --> 27:38.700
but I'm going
to sock it to you anyway.

27:38.744 --> 27:42.225
I'm Bebe DeBarge,
and this is my house.

27:42.269 --> 27:46.577
And that is my imported
strawberry daiquiri syrup

27:46.621 --> 27:48.362
that you're guzzling down.

27:48.405 --> 27:50.146
- Hey!

27:50.190 --> 27:51.800
I was drinking that.

27:51.844 --> 27:54.150
- You were, and now you're not.

27:54.194 --> 27:57.676
Listen to me,
you little gold-digging whore--

27:57.719 --> 27:59.808
- N-no, that's not
what I said at all!

27:59.852 --> 28:01.810
- Girl to girl...

28:01.854 --> 28:04.770
It's not that
I can't empathize.

28:04.813 --> 28:07.468
I remember when it was me
in your shoes.

28:07.511 --> 28:11.559
I had just gotten off the bus
from some dusty nowhere

28:11.602 --> 28:14.823
and trying to make my way
up to the top

28:14.867 --> 28:16.825
in the big city

28:16.869 --> 28:18.871
with nothing but my smarts,
my talents,

28:18.914 --> 28:20.916
and my God-given sex appeal.

28:20.960 --> 28:25.834
I know your game because
I played it in spades, baby.

28:25.878 --> 28:29.838
But my Sonny is off limits.

28:29.882 --> 28:33.712
So why don't you just
pack up your act

28:33.755 --> 28:35.975
and take it somewhere else?

28:36.018 --> 28:38.673
- Lady...

28:38.717 --> 28:42.372
I don't understand
half of what you just said.

28:42.416 --> 28:44.853
But if you're trying

28:44.897 --> 28:48.814
to get laid out
on your dusty ass,

28:48.857 --> 28:51.817
you said it to the right bitch.

28:51.860 --> 28:54.210
- No!
- Ladies.

28:54.254 --> 28:55.777
You've met.

28:55.821 --> 28:57.387
How delightful.

28:57.431 --> 28:59.650
- Well, hello, handsome.

28:59.694 --> 29:02.131
- He sure is.

29:02.175 --> 29:04.917
- Oh, Bebe, Bebe,

29:04.960 --> 29:07.484
my Bebe.

29:07.528 --> 29:09.791
Run along, now, Bebe.

29:09.835 --> 29:11.793
The boys are getting lonely.

29:11.837 --> 29:15.014
I'll take care of this.
- Mm.

29:16.755 --> 29:19.409
[tense music]

29:19.453 --> 29:23.936
♪

29:23.979 --> 29:26.590
- [sighs]
Look at you.

29:26.634 --> 29:30.681
♪

29:30.725 --> 29:34.337
This blush of new life

29:34.381 --> 29:36.600
so becomes you, Amanda.

29:36.644 --> 29:38.646
- Keep talking.

29:38.689 --> 29:42.215
- I am...

29:42.258 --> 29:44.826
amazed.

29:44.870 --> 29:48.395
Can this really be true?

29:48.438 --> 29:51.615
I have lived for eons...

29:51.659 --> 29:54.488
and yet there is still...

29:54.531 --> 29:56.098
newness.

29:56.142 --> 29:57.796
♪

29:57.839 --> 30:00.450
Still moments of wonder.

30:00.494 --> 30:02.626
♪

30:02.670 --> 30:05.542
- [breathing shakily]

30:05.586 --> 30:08.154
- [gags, grunts]

30:13.028 --> 30:15.291
- Looks like it's time
for us to go.

30:15.335 --> 30:17.816
- [laughing]

30:20.340 --> 30:22.951
[Amanda laughing]

30:22.995 --> 30:25.127
- Uh, A-Amanda, I--
- Oh!

30:25.171 --> 30:26.825
- I thought I had
the address wrong.

30:26.868 --> 30:29.784
- It's you
with the pretty eyes!

30:29.828 --> 30:33.135
Come with me,
we're having a baby!

30:33.179 --> 30:34.833
- Wait, what?

30:34.876 --> 30:37.836
It--it can't be mine.
- Of course not, silly.

30:37.879 --> 30:41.448
- It doesn't matter.
I'll stay with you.

30:41.491 --> 30:43.319
I've always dreamed
of having a family.

30:43.363 --> 30:46.279
We'll raise this baby together,
and I will love it like my own.

30:46.322 --> 30:47.236
- [laughs]

30:47.280 --> 30:48.977
- We'll follow
our blessed baby.

30:49.021 --> 30:50.849
Walk it like we talk it.
- [laughs]

30:50.892 --> 30:53.025
- Who the fuck are you?

30:53.068 --> 30:55.897
- I don't particularly
appreciate your tone, friend.

30:55.941 --> 30:58.247
[dark music]

30:58.291 --> 31:00.162
[chokes]

31:00.206 --> 31:05.080
♪

31:05.124 --> 31:06.734
[chokes]

31:06.777 --> 31:09.345
[door closes]

31:09.389 --> 31:12.348
[choking]

31:12.392 --> 31:14.350
♪

31:14.394 --> 31:16.222
[engine turning over]

31:16.265 --> 31:18.528
[whimpers]

31:18.572 --> 31:21.009
[thud]

31:21.053 --> 31:24.012
- Aw, he was nice.

31:24.056 --> 31:27.276
- [laughs] We're going to see
the doctor now.

31:33.065 --> 31:35.023
- What's the matter
with you, Sax?

31:35.067 --> 31:36.851
Ain't you even gonna
fight back?

31:36.895 --> 31:39.419
- It's no fun
if you're just gonna lie there.

31:39.462 --> 31:41.900
- Yeah, at least pretend
to be into this.

31:41.943 --> 31:45.033
- Well...

31:45.077 --> 31:47.644
sure, I mean, if it'll help.

31:50.647 --> 31:54.042
- Nick Sax.
- Is my table ready?

31:54.086 --> 31:57.263
- Get the fuck out.

31:59.004 --> 32:01.267
You fucking loser.
- [chuckles]

32:01.310 --> 32:03.399
- Oh, I guess it was
only a matter of time

32:03.443 --> 32:05.706
before you ended up
on this side of the bars,

32:05.749 --> 32:06.794
huh, chief?

32:06.837 --> 32:08.448
- [grunts]

32:08.491 --> 32:10.580
- Got two options.

32:10.624 --> 32:13.279
We can do this the hard way...

32:13.322 --> 32:15.934
or we can do it
the rock-hard way.

32:15.977 --> 32:18.762
- Do you even need to ask?
- Well, not really.

32:18.806 --> 32:20.068
[Taser crackling]

32:20.112 --> 32:23.245
[door opens, closes]

32:23.289 --> 32:26.292
[peppy country music playing
over speakers]

32:26.335 --> 32:30.426
- Howdy, partner.
Welcome to Western Buffet.

32:30.470 --> 32:37.520
♪

32:41.133 --> 32:43.091
- We'd come here
once a month--

32:43.135 --> 32:45.311
our big night out.

32:45.354 --> 32:49.141
I used to look so forward
to it.

32:49.184 --> 32:51.447
You could have anything
you wanted.

32:51.491 --> 32:55.625
♪

32:55.669 --> 32:59.107
- Is it like you remember?

32:59.151 --> 33:02.154
- No, it's not the same.

33:02.197 --> 33:06.027
Nothing stays the same.

33:06.071 --> 33:09.335
People change.

33:09.378 --> 33:13.208
♪

33:13.252 --> 33:15.819
Oh.

33:15.863 --> 33:17.082
The jukebox--

33:17.125 --> 33:20.215
that was the best.

33:20.259 --> 33:22.696
I-if you grow up
in a town like this,

33:22.739 --> 33:24.915
sometimes music
is all you have.

33:24.959 --> 33:28.006
♪

33:28.049 --> 33:30.660
- Sometimes
when I can't sleep,

33:30.704 --> 33:34.055
I put on my headphones
and listen to music all night.

33:34.099 --> 33:38.320
It keeps you
from thinking about...

33:38.364 --> 33:39.843
things.

33:39.887 --> 33:42.020
♪

33:42.063 --> 33:45.371
Y-your dad, was he really bad?

33:45.414 --> 33:48.113
♪

33:48.156 --> 33:51.290
- [gulps]
Uh, well...

33:51.333 --> 33:54.684
let's just say I didn't have
to look outside the house

33:54.728 --> 33:57.078
to find monsters.

33:57.122 --> 33:59.820
Alcoholic, violent temper.

33:59.863 --> 34:02.997
Sounds familiar, I guess.

34:03.041 --> 34:04.912
- My dad would never hurt me.

34:04.955 --> 34:09.047
♪

34:09.090 --> 34:12.267
- Uh, Cheryl managed
to get us away from him.

34:12.311 --> 34:15.531
If she hadn't done it...

34:15.575 --> 34:19.448
he would have
eventually killed us both.

34:19.492 --> 34:22.364
- Where did he go?

34:22.408 --> 34:24.453
- Not far.

34:24.497 --> 34:27.065
♪

34:27.108 --> 34:31.373
[sniffs] Ah, I just had
the silliest idea.

34:31.417 --> 34:33.332
- I don't know any
of these songs.

34:33.375 --> 34:37.771
They're all old.
- [chuckles]

34:37.814 --> 34:40.426
This one.

34:42.906 --> 34:46.084
[Tears for Fears' "Everybody
Wants to Rule the World"]

34:46.127 --> 34:53.308
♪

35:11.761 --> 35:15.939
- ♪ Welcome to your life

35:15.983 --> 35:20.030
♪ There's no turning back

35:20.074 --> 35:24.774
♪ Even while we sleep

35:24.818 --> 35:26.907
♪ We will find you

35:26.950 --> 35:31.172
♪ Acting on your
best behavior ♪

35:31.216 --> 35:35.437
♪ Turn your back
on Mother Nature ♪

35:35.481 --> 35:40.790
♪ Everybody wants
to rule the world ♪

35:40.834 --> 35:44.142
♪

35:44.185 --> 35:48.276
♪ Help me to decide

35:48.320 --> 35:52.889
♪ Help me make the most
of freedom ♪

35:52.933 --> 35:54.978
♪ And of pleasure

35:55.022 --> 35:59.157
♪ Nothing ever lasts forever

35:59.200 --> 36:03.465
♪ Everybody wants
to rule the world ♪

36:03.509 --> 36:05.685
[music fades]
- [grunts]

36:05.728 --> 36:09.776
[distant sirens wailing]

36:09.819 --> 36:13.823
[grunts]

36:13.867 --> 36:17.087
- [smooches]

36:17.131 --> 36:19.568
- You're welcome.

36:20.830 --> 36:22.441
- Do I want to know
how you swung this?

36:22.484 --> 36:23.659
- Don't ask.
- Don't tell.

36:23.703 --> 36:25.313
- Look, Sax,
I can't sugarcoat this.

36:25.357 --> 36:27.185
Since I last saw you
things have gone from weird

36:27.228 --> 36:28.838
to, like, super fucking weird.

36:28.882 --> 36:31.450
Blue has escaped from prison,
only he isn't Blue.

36:31.493 --> 36:33.365
He's gonna kill Sonny
on live TV.

36:33.408 --> 36:35.410
- Sounds great.
I'll set my DVR.

36:41.068 --> 36:44.811
Just give me a moment.
It's gonna feel so much better.

36:44.854 --> 36:47.161
[grunts]

36:47.205 --> 36:49.207
Oh, yeah,
like lancing a hemorrhoid.

36:49.250 --> 36:51.687
Now, where were we?
Mer, look...

36:51.731 --> 36:54.124
I can see that you've got
a nice, comfortable seat

36:54.168 --> 36:56.083
on the observation car
of the crazy train,

36:56.126 --> 36:57.693
but I need you to stay here.

36:57.737 --> 36:58.825
Here.

36:58.868 --> 37:00.218
And by here, I mean reality.

37:00.261 --> 37:01.436
I can't do this alone.

37:01.480 --> 37:03.046
- Sax, this has been
about Sonny's Easter show

37:03.090 --> 37:04.134
the entire time.

37:04.178 --> 37:06.136
- Mer, I don't give
a shit omelet

37:06.180 --> 37:07.355
about Sonny's Easter show!

37:07.399 --> 37:09.227
I care about one thing--
my family.

37:09.270 --> 37:10.358
- Yes, your family!

37:10.402 --> 37:11.577
They're all
a part of this, too.

37:11.620 --> 37:13.231
I don't know exactly--
- Nick!

37:13.274 --> 37:14.536
- Hold that thought.
What?

37:14.580 --> 37:16.756
- Nick, I found Amanda.
I know where she is.

37:16.799 --> 37:17.800
We got to hurry, Nick.

37:17.844 --> 37:19.324
I-I mean,
we really got to hurry!

37:19.367 --> 37:21.064
- Copy, hurry. Mer, I can't
tell you how I know this--

37:21.108 --> 37:22.327
- Amanda.
- Yeah.

37:22.370 --> 37:23.502
- I don't care how you know.
Let's go get her.

37:23.545 --> 37:25.243
- Great,
and then we'll take care

37:25.286 --> 37:26.722
of Sonny Shine's
little Easter show later.

37:26.766 --> 37:30.073
- Oh, don't worry about that.
I took care of it already.

37:30.117 --> 37:32.902
- Oh, shit, my car, too?
- Yeah.

37:32.946 --> 37:35.340
- Wow, you must've been digging
deep down in that thing.

37:35.383 --> 37:37.037
- Oh, good God.
- [grunts]

37:38.952 --> 37:40.997
- This is a great honor.

37:43.173 --> 37:45.480
I've been providing
quality programming

37:45.524 --> 37:47.743
for children of all ages
on this network

37:47.787 --> 37:49.310
for over a decade.

37:49.354 --> 37:52.400
I've done more upfronts
than Matt Lauer.

37:52.444 --> 37:54.576
[laughs]
But to be called before

37:54.620 --> 37:57.231
the esteemed Board of Directors

37:57.275 --> 37:59.233
on the eve
of my greatest triumph,

37:59.277 --> 38:01.888
all I can say
is I've never felt

38:01.931 --> 38:03.368
such a sense of family.

38:03.411 --> 38:05.283
I've never felt--
- Shine.

38:05.326 --> 38:07.502
We didn't call you here
to wish you good luck.

38:07.546 --> 38:09.852
- Your special's off.

38:09.896 --> 38:11.071
- "Off"?

38:11.114 --> 38:12.768
- Canceled.

38:12.812 --> 38:14.248
- But Easter's tomorrow.

38:14.292 --> 38:15.597
- That's correct.

38:15.641 --> 38:17.730
The public has been through
a lot this year.

38:17.773 --> 38:19.558
These Easter Bunny
terrorist attacks

38:19.601 --> 38:22.125
have cast a pall
on the entire season.

38:22.169 --> 38:23.779
Then the events
of this morning,

38:23.823 --> 38:26.304
which were a terrible shock
to all of us.

38:26.347 --> 38:28.697
But this so-called
"Eggtacular"...

38:28.741 --> 38:30.308
- Honestly, Shine,

38:30.351 --> 38:32.919
haven't the people
suffered enough?

38:32.962 --> 38:36.139
- I'm going to save Easter.

38:36.183 --> 38:37.924
- Not this year

38:37.967 --> 38:39.882
and not on our network.

38:39.926 --> 38:43.451
- [smacks lips]
I think Kap Gostynski

38:43.495 --> 38:46.324
will have something
to say about that.

38:46.367 --> 38:48.151
- Gostynski?

38:48.195 --> 38:49.675
- Didn't you hear?

38:49.718 --> 38:52.504
- And this just in--
shocking footage has emerged

38:52.547 --> 38:55.637
of famed TV executive
Kap Gostynski

38:55.681 --> 38:58.074
appearing to cannibalize
his young nephew.

38:58.118 --> 39:01.382
Warning to our audiences--
this footage will be graphic.

39:01.426 --> 39:04.559
- [screaming]
- Is that you?

39:04.603 --> 39:07.170
- [grunting]
- [screaming]

39:07.214 --> 39:09.172
[telephone ringing]
- Hold my calls.

39:09.216 --> 39:11.000
- I mean really
disturbing footage.

39:11.044 --> 39:12.611
If I were Kap Gostynski,

39:12.654 --> 39:16.179
I would certainly think
about killing myself.

39:16.223 --> 39:17.355
Well, you know what?

39:17.398 --> 39:18.965
Why don't we show it
one more time

39:19.008 --> 39:21.184
for our viewers
that are just joining us?

39:21.228 --> 39:24.187
[suspenseful music]

39:24.231 --> 39:28.191
♪

39:28.235 --> 39:29.671
[blade slices]

39:29.715 --> 39:31.369
♪

39:31.412 --> 39:32.761
- Oh, shit.

39:34.850 --> 39:36.286
- ♪ Everybody wants...
- Oh...

39:36.330 --> 39:37.592
- [laughs]

39:37.636 --> 39:40.421
- That was the most fun
I have had since--

39:40.465 --> 39:42.641
[distant grunting]

39:42.684 --> 39:44.730
- What is it?

39:44.773 --> 39:47.559
- Did you hear that?

39:47.602 --> 39:49.952
Listen.

39:49.996 --> 39:53.173
[faint gurgling, whimpering]

39:53.216 --> 39:56.176
[dark, curious music]

39:56.219 --> 40:03.270
♪

40:28.164 --> 40:31.777
- We've got to get him
to a doctor.

40:31.820 --> 40:34.997
[sinister music]

40:35.041 --> 40:42.048
♪

40:46.661 --> 40:48.054
It's him.

40:49.708 --> 40:51.013
Why did you bring me here?

40:51.057 --> 40:52.711
- My mother lives
in fear every day

40:52.754 --> 40:54.843
that he will come back
to finish what he started.

40:54.887 --> 40:57.890
I can't bear
to see her this way.

40:57.933 --> 41:00.196
I've warned him,
threatened him.

41:00.240 --> 41:03.199
But now I'm gonna do what
I should have done years ago.

41:03.243 --> 41:06.507
- When you left earlier,
this is what you were doing.

41:06.551 --> 41:08.683
♪

41:08.727 --> 41:11.425
- Don't you see?

41:11.469 --> 41:14.559
I've spent my whole life
trying to find the courage

41:14.602 --> 41:16.474
to face this moment.

41:16.517 --> 41:18.911
He did things to us...

41:18.954 --> 41:21.870
things that I cannot repeat,

41:21.914 --> 41:25.787
things that I cannot bear
to remember.

41:25.831 --> 41:28.224
I was powerless, Hailey.

41:28.268 --> 41:30.313
♪

41:30.357 --> 41:32.228
But not anymore.

41:32.272 --> 41:35.231
If you can find the courage
to do what needs to be done,

41:35.275 --> 41:36.711
then so can I.

41:36.755 --> 41:39.540
You're my inspiration.

41:39.584 --> 41:42.761
- You're going to kill him.

41:42.804 --> 41:45.503
- Sometimes bad people

41:45.546 --> 41:47.548
need to die.

41:47.592 --> 41:49.245
But don't think of it
as revenge.

41:49.289 --> 41:51.813
Think of it as
doing what needs to be done

41:51.857 --> 41:55.251
because you are the only one
with the courage to do it.

41:55.295 --> 41:59.473
And when it's over,
the world is more...

41:59.517 --> 42:00.561
correct.

42:00.605 --> 42:02.911
That's all.

42:02.955 --> 42:04.478
I've given him a drug.

42:04.522 --> 42:07.437
It'll deaden his nerves
so he won't feel a thing.

42:07.481 --> 42:10.615
[beer can clangs]
Shh, shh, shh. Try to relax.

42:10.658 --> 42:14.488
It will take you days to die.

42:14.532 --> 42:17.360
But all the while,

42:17.404 --> 42:19.624
your nerves will be vividly,

42:19.667 --> 42:23.279
exquisitely alive.

42:23.323 --> 42:26.761
You will feel...

42:26.805 --> 42:29.590
everything.

42:29.634 --> 42:31.810
You can look away
if you want to.

42:31.853 --> 42:35.030
[suspenseful music]

42:35.074 --> 42:36.771
♪

42:36.815 --> 42:39.034
- It has to be this way

42:39.078 --> 42:41.646
because of everything you did.

42:41.689 --> 42:43.604
Do you understand?

42:43.648 --> 42:46.302
♪

42:46.346 --> 42:49.175
- Who are you?

42:49.218 --> 42:55.964
♪

42:56.008 --> 42:58.880
- It'll be over soon.

43:04.016 --> 43:07.149
[dramatic music]

43:07.193 --> 43:14.243
♪

43:16.768 --> 43:18.987
- We're done here.

43:19.031 --> 43:21.381
We're going back to the city.

43:21.424 --> 43:23.644
You needed
to make a friend of death,

43:23.688 --> 43:26.516
and now you have.

43:26.560 --> 43:28.475
♪

43:28.518 --> 43:30.520
You're ready.

43:30.564 --> 43:32.218
- Ready?

43:32.261 --> 43:33.611
For what?

43:33.654 --> 43:36.439
♪

43:36.483 --> 43:39.834
- You're gonna do what
your father should have done...

43:39.878 --> 43:42.663
what I should have done.

43:42.707 --> 43:47.320
You're gonna kill the one
who stole your childhood...

43:47.363 --> 43:49.844
your innocence.

43:49.888 --> 43:52.673
♪

43:52.717 --> 43:54.370
- Sonny Shine.

43:54.414 --> 43:59.027
♪

43:59.071 --> 44:00.594
[siren wailing]

44:00.638 --> 44:03.510
- Well, well,
back at General.

44:03.553 --> 44:05.643
- Yeah, I'm getting misty
just thinking about it.

44:05.686 --> 44:08.384
Last time I was in that joint,
I had to shoot my way out.

44:08.428 --> 44:12.824
- Yeah, well, we might have
to shoot our way in this time.

44:12.867 --> 44:15.391
- I love when you talk dirty
to me.

44:15.435 --> 44:18.351
- How could Amanda ever end up
in such an awful place, Nick?

44:18.394 --> 44:21.049
- Consorting with
the wrong sort of people, Hap.

44:21.093 --> 44:24.096
- We're gonna need
to find another way in.

44:27.055 --> 44:28.709
- I like this way.

44:28.753 --> 44:30.711
- Nick. Nick.
- What?

44:30.755 --> 44:32.365
- They have Amanda in there.

44:32.408 --> 44:34.715
It's better if they don't know
we're coming.

44:34.759 --> 44:36.543
[thunder booms]

44:36.586 --> 44:37.805
Is it yours?

44:37.849 --> 44:39.546
She said she was
getting back into dating.

44:39.589 --> 44:40.678
- Oh, for crying out loud,

44:40.721 --> 44:42.027
can we just change
the subject, please?

44:42.070 --> 44:43.637
I'm trying to focus
on the loss of human life

44:43.681 --> 44:45.247
I'm about to inflict.

44:45.291 --> 44:48.120
- Sorry.

44:48.163 --> 44:50.078
- Jesus.

44:50.122 --> 44:52.602
- Oh, shit, I forgot
to tell you the best part.

44:52.646 --> 44:54.039
- N-Nick?
- Sockatoo.

44:54.082 --> 44:55.518
- Hey, Nick.
- You know, the Wishee--

44:55.562 --> 44:56.781
the one we tried to cut open?
- Did you see something?

44:56.824 --> 44:58.260
- Okay, all right, stop.
You know something?

44:58.304 --> 45:00.262
You've been interrupting
an awful lot.

45:00.306 --> 45:01.916
I mean, if you got
something to tell me,

45:01.960 --> 45:03.439
why don't you--holy shit!

45:03.483 --> 45:06.181
[suspenseful music]

45:06.225 --> 45:11.709
♪

45:11.752 --> 45:14.668
What the--

45:14.712 --> 45:17.279
- [screeches]
- Uh-oh.

45:17.323 --> 45:21.762
♪

45:21.806 --> 45:22.763
- Nick!

45:22.807 --> 45:26.201
♪

45:26.245 --> 45:28.377
Lady!

45:28.421 --> 45:30.902
♪

45:30.945 --> 45:33.556
Lady, wake up!

45:33.600 --> 45:37.647
♪

45:37.691 --> 45:39.954
[Nick mumbling indistinctly]

45:39.998 --> 45:44.306
♪

45:44.350 --> 45:46.395
[Nick grunts]

45:48.702 --> 45:50.138
♪

45:50.182 --> 45:52.314
- All right, sandwich lover.

45:52.358 --> 45:54.099
♪

45:54.142 --> 45:56.884
[gun cocks, gunshot]

45:56.928 --> 45:59.365
[body thuds]

45:59.408 --> 46:00.801
♪

46:00.845 --> 46:03.978
[grunting]

46:04.022 --> 46:09.375
♪

46:09.418 --> 46:11.159
[Wishee farts]

46:11.203 --> 46:14.380
Look, Mer,
it does have an asshole.

46:14.423 --> 46:21.474
♪

46:23.041 --> 46:26.261
[distant siren wailing]

46:26.305 --> 46:28.437
Well...

46:28.481 --> 46:31.658
that happened.

46:31.701 --> 46:33.399
[spits]

46:39.753 --> 46:42.277
[door closes]

46:49.894 --> 46:52.635
- Where is everybody?

46:52.679 --> 46:54.202
[PA beeps]

46:54.246 --> 46:56.683
[indistinct announcements
over PA]

46:56.726 --> 47:03.211
♪

47:03.255 --> 47:06.171
- Your little tramp
is in the hospital.

47:06.214 --> 47:09.174
- Oh!
[grunts]

47:09.217 --> 47:12.873
- Don't you want to see
if it's a boy or a girl?

47:12.917 --> 47:14.962
- Are you insane?

47:15.006 --> 47:17.704
The seed of my loins...

47:17.747 --> 47:19.880
is my work,

47:19.924 --> 47:21.882
my art,

47:21.926 --> 47:24.667
my Eggtacular.

47:24.711 --> 47:28.715
And it's kaput!

47:28.758 --> 47:31.239
- Well, then what about this?

47:31.283 --> 47:33.154
- You silly, silly woman.

47:33.198 --> 47:35.374
- [breathing heavily]
[monitor beeping]

47:35.417 --> 47:39.552
- The baby inside
Amanda Hansen isn't mine.

47:39.595 --> 47:42.294
♪

47:42.337 --> 47:44.252
[Wishees screeching]

47:44.296 --> 47:47.081
- What's going on?
Why are they here?

47:47.125 --> 47:48.604
- Heart rate's
going through the roof.

47:48.648 --> 47:50.911
We're gonna lose her.

47:50.955 --> 47:52.870
- [whispering]
It's theirs.

47:52.913 --> 47:54.480
♪

47:54.523 --> 47:57.570
- [screaming]
